Quote:  We learn from the Wellington Post that one of the first uses made of the Australian cable was by a remittance man. He telegraphed to his friends in England "Lend me GBP20." The answer received was "Paid for your telegram and this - balance per mail." He is now waiting for the mail that will bring him about enough to acknowledge the receipt by post.
